                                <p>Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 4 double raised binds and 2 endbands. Pinclasps with anchorplates on <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/> and pins on <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>, lower right corner: the National Library green book label with printed and handwritten text: <quote xml:lang="sv">Hs-Bibliotheket, Stockholm. Handskrifter. Kyrkohistoria. Sv. Medeltid</quote>. <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>, at the top in black ink: <quote>F I</quote>; in the centre a parchment label with text in black ink, partly worn off: <quote xml:lang="la">Attestaciones b<unclear quantity="4" unit="chars" reason="illegible"/> F I</quote>. On <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>: branded on the leather: <quote>74</quote>; on a white label, partly torn off:<quote> A 14</quote>; at the bottom in gold:<quote> A 14</quote>
                                </p>
