                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>Written by Italian scribes c. <origDate when="1391">1391</origDate> in <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100070">Rome</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, see <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107108">Collijn (1924–1931)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="iv" to="vii" unit="page"/>
                                    <citedRange from="xiv" to="xiv" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Belonged to the library of <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100101">Vadstena</placeName> monastery as attested to by the Vadstena shelfmark <quote>F I 4us</quote> on the <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>, and by <quote>F I</quote> in ink on the <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/> and on the bottom line of the label, now almost illegible.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>To the Royal Chancery in 1620 and in the 1670s to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>, see <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107108">Collijn (1924–1931)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="v" to="vi" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>. The manuscript is listed in the archive's inventories: in the inventories from 1720, 90:2, and 1722, U 90:4, as <quote>74</quote> (as seen on <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>); in U 91:2:1 as <quote>G 74</quote> (the letter <quote>G</quote> written in the lower left corner on <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>); in U 91:5 as <quote>6</quote> (as written on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>). In the last two inventories, <quote>14</quote> has been added to the older signum. The current signum is used for the first time in Helin's inventory U 91:2:2.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>From the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName> to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">Royal library</orgName> in 1780.</p>
                        </acquisition>
