                                    <foliation>Contemporary foliation in brown-black ink (by same scribe as some of the marginal notes?): i-xxi (<locus from="2r" to="22r" scheme="folios"/>). <locus from="23r" to="23r" scheme="folios"/> is blank without original foliation. Leaf numbering in red in the lower left corner of each verso running from <quote>a ii</quote> to <quote>b v</quote>, starts on <locus from="3v" to="3v" scheme="folios"/> (<quote>a i</quote> was probably in the lower corner of <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/> but is now lost). Pagination running from <quote>a 4</quote> to <quote>a 40</quote> in pale lead point in the middle of the lower margin visible on <locus from="3v" to="21v" scheme="folios"/>, on some pages barely visible. <secFol>eorumdem et in</secFol>
                                    </foliation>
